com.digi.xbee.api.models

Class XBee64BitAddress

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.digi.xbee.api.models.XBee64BitAddress

  • public final class XBee64BitAddress
extends Object
    This class represents a 64-bit address (also known as MAC address).

    The 64-bit address is a unique device address assigned during manufacturing. This address is unique to each physical device.

      • XBee64BitAddress

        public XBee64BitAddress(String address)
        Class constructor. Instantiates a new object of type XBee64BitAddress with the given parameters.

        The string must be the hexadecimal representation of a 64-bit address.

        Parameters:
        address - The XBee 64-bit address as string.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if address.length() < 1 or if address contains non-hexadecimal characters and is longer than 8 bytes.
